cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for automated quantification of mouse behaviors from videos, which involves object tracking and deep learning-based mouse part detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed Bayesian Integer Linear Programming Model also involves optimization and geometric constraints, which could place the paper in the optimization (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
